Package proj78.xml.parser

Interface Summary
XmlParseEventListener Allows for implementing classes to register themselves with an XML parser and be notified of the significant parse events that are generated by it.
 

Class Summary
XmlDocumentBuilder Builds a DOM tree step-by-step, by translating the parse events that are generated by an XML parser into node creation calls.
XmlParser An XmlParser object takes a string or some other source of XML as its input and processes it, generating significant parse events along the way.
XmlParser.Scanner Scans over a source of textual input one character at a time.
XmlParserFactory Provides a single static createParser() method, through which the application can obtain an XML parser.
XmlParserImpl Concrete XmlParser subclass.
 

Exception Summary
XmlParseException The exception that is thrown to indicate a parse error.
